subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat.
Close to villages and in disturbed habitat, regrowth vegetation, agricultural fields, and tall grasslands of 
Imperata
and cane grasses (both 
Poaceae
). The Pacific Rat is rarely found in primary habitat, but in places where there are few surviving native rodent species, such as the mountains of Timor, it can commonly be found in primary habitats. It can usually coexistwith or be outcompeted by the Roof Rat (
R. rattus
) or the Oriental House Rat (
R. tanezumi
) in villages.
